casebody.data:
WILLIAM WINGERT v. DANIEL W. DOUB et al. [Nos. 84-86,

October Term, 1928.]

Decided December 7th, 1928.

The causes were argued before Bond, C. J., Ubneb, Adkins, Oeeutt, Pabke, and Sloan, JJ.

William Wingert, with whom were H. F. Wingert and Miller Wingert on the brief, for the appellant. Daniel W. Doub, with whom was BobeH H. McCauley on the brief, for the appellees.

A

per curiam

opinion was filed, dismissing the appeals.
